Note:
Runa Standard Library: Memory Profiling and Analysis

Production-grade memory profiling providing comprehensive allocation tracking,
leak detection, fragmentation analysis, and optimization guidance surpassing
Python's tracemalloc, Rust's valgrind, Java's JProfiler, and C++'s AddressSanitizer.

Features:
- Real-time allocation and deallocation tracking with stack traces
- Advanced memory leak detection with confidence scoring
- Memory fragmentation analysis and optimization suggestions
- Heap visualization and memory layout analysis
- Memory access pattern profiling and cache optimization
- Garbage collection analysis and optimization
- Memory pool and allocator performance monitoring
- Virtual memory usage tracking and optimization
- Memory bandwidth and latency profiling
- Cross-platform memory management integration
- Production-safe low-overhead tracking
- Memory corruption detection and prevention
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "../../string" as String
Import "../../datetime" as DateTime
Import "os/os" as OS

Note: Memory profiling types and structures
Type called "MemoryProfiler":
    profiler_id as String
    is_active as Boolean
    start_time as DateTime.DateTime
    end_time as DateTime.DateTime
    total_allocations as Integer
    total_deallocations as Integer
    bytes_allocated as Integer
    bytes_deallocated as Integer
    peak_memory_usage as Integer
    current_memory_usage as Integer
    allocation_map as Dictionary[Integer, AllocationRecord]
    deallocation_history as List[DeallocationRecord]
    memory_snapshots as List[MemorySnapshot]
    fragmentation_reports as List[FragmentationReport]
    leak_reports as List[LeakReport]
    configuration as MemoryProfilerConfig

Type called "MemoryProfilerConfig":
    track_allocations as Boolean
    track_stack_traces as Boolean
    track_call_sites as Boolean
    enable_leak_detection as Boolean
    enable_fragmentation_analysis as Boolean
    enable_heap_profiling as Boolean
    max_stack_depth as Integer
    sampling_rate as Float
    min_allocation_size as Integer
    snapshot_interval_ms as Integer
    leak_detection_threshold_ms as Integer
    memory_pattern_analysis as Boolean

Type called "AllocationRecord":
    allocation_id as Integer
    address as Integer
    size as Integer
    timestamp as DateTime.DateTime
    thread_id as Integer
    stack_trace as List[StackFrame]
    call_site as CallSite
    allocation_type as AllocationType
    alignment as Integer
    lifetime_ms as Integer
    access_pattern as AccessPattern
    is_leaked as Boolean

Type called "DeallocationRecord":
    allocation_id as Integer
    address as Integer
    size as Integer
    allocation_time as DateTime.DateTime
    deallocation_time as DateTime.DateTime
    lifetime_ms as Integer
    thread_id as Integer
    stack_trace as List[StackFrame]
    call_site as CallSite

Type AllocationType is:
    | Malloc
    | Calloc
    | Realloc
    | New
    | NewArray
    | Custom
    | Stack
    | Global

Type called "CallSite":
    function_name as String
    module_name as String
    file_name as String
    line_number as Integer
    call_count as Integer
    total_bytes_allocated as Integer
    average_allocation_size as Float

Type called "StackFrame":
    function_name as String
    module_name as String
    file_name as String
    line_number as Integer
    instruction_pointer as Integer
    frame_pointer as Integer

Type called "AccessPattern":
    read_count as Integer
    write_count as Integer
    first_access_time as DateTime.DateTime
    last_access_time as DateTime.DateTime
    access_frequency_hz as Float
    sequential_accesses as Integer
    random_accesses as Integer
    cache_hits as Integer
    cache_misses as Integer

Type called "MemorySnapshot":
    timestamp as DateTime.DateTime
    total_allocated_bytes as Integer
    total_free_bytes as Integer
    heap_size as Integer
    stack_size as Integer
    mapped_memory as Integer
    virtual_memory as Integer
    resident_memory as Integer
    shared_memory as Integer
    allocation_count as Integer
    active_allocations as Integer
    fragmentation_ratio as Float
    memory_efficiency as Float

Type called "FragmentationReport":
    timestamp as DateTime.DateTime
    total_heap_size as Integer
    used_heap_size as Integer
    free_heap_size as Integer
    largest_free_block as Integer
    free_block_count as Integer
    fragmentation_ratio as Float
    external_fragmentation as Float
    internal_fragmentation as Float
    memory_waste_bytes as Integer
    allocation_overhead as Float
    recommendations as List[String]

Type called "LeakReport":
    timestamp as DateTime.DateTime
    leaked_allocations as List[AllocationRecord]
    total_leaked_bytes as Integer
    leak_confidence_score as Float
    suspected_leak_sources as List[CallSite]
    leak_growth_rate as Float
    leak_severity as LeakSeverity
    remediation_suggestions as List[String]

Type LeakSeverity is:
    | Low
    | Medium
    | High
    | Critical

Type called "MemoryPool":
    pool_id as String
    pool_name as String
    total_size as Integer
    used_size as Integer
    free_size as Integer
    block_size as Integer
    block_count as Integer
    free_blocks as Integer
    allocation_speed_ns as Integer
    deallocation_speed_ns as Integer
    fragmentation_ratio as Float

Type called "HeapVisualization":
    heap_segments as List[HeapSegment]
    memory_layout as List[MemoryRegion]
    allocation_density_map as Dictionary[Integer, Integer]
    hotspot_regions as List[HotspotRegion]
    fragmentation_map as Dictionary[Integer, Float]

Type called "HeapSegment":
    start_address as Integer
    end_address as Integer
    size as Integer
    segment_type as SegmentType
    is_mapped as Boolean
    permissions as String
    usage_percentage as Float

Type SegmentType is:
    | Heap
    | Stack
    | Code
    | Data
    | Shared
    | Anonymous

Type called "MemoryRegion":
    start_address as Integer
    size as Integer
    region_type as RegionType
    allocation_count as Integer
    access_frequency as Integer
    last_access_time as DateTime.DateTime

Type RegionType is:
    | Allocated
    | Free
    | Reserved
    | Committed
    | Protected

Type called "HotspotRegion":
    start_address as Integer
    size as Integer
    allocation_density as Float
    access_frequency as Integer
    heat_score as Float
    primary_allocation_source as String

Note: Core memory profiling operations
Process called "create_memory_profiler" that takes config as MemoryProfilerConfig returns MemoryProfiler:
    Let profiler_id be generate_memory_profiler_id() Return MemoryProfiler with:
    profiler_id as profiler_id
    is_active as false
    start_time as DateTime.now()
    end_time as DateTime.now()
    total_allocations as 0
    total_deallocations as 0
    bytes_allocated as 0
    bytes_deallocated as 0
    peak_memory_usage as 0
    current_memory_usage as 0
    allocation_map as dictionary
    deallocation_history as list
    memory_snapshots as list
    fragmentation_reports as list
    leak_reports as list
    configuration as config

Process called "start_memory_profiling" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Boolean:
    If profiler.is_active:
    Return false Set profiler.is_active to true
    Set profiler.start_time to DateTime.now() Clear profiler.allocation_map
    Clear profiler.deallocation_history
    Clear profiler.memory_snapshots
    Clear profiler.fragmentation_reports
    Clear profiler.leak_reports Set profiler.total_allocations to 0
    Set profiler.total_deallocations to 0
    Set profiler.bytes_allocated to 0
    Set profiler.bytes_deallocated to 0
    Set profiler.current_memory_usage to 0
    Set profiler.peak_memory_usage to 0 Let initialization_result be initialize_memory_tracking with profiler as profiler
    If not initialization_result:
    Set profiler.is_active to false
    Return false start_memory_monitoring_thread with profiler as profiler Return true

Process called "stop_memory_profiling" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Boolean:
    If not profiler.is_active:
    Return false Set profiler.is_active to false
    Set profiler.end_time to DateTime.now() stop_memory_monitoring_thread with profiler as profiler If profiler.configuration.enable_leak_detection:
    generate_final_leak_report with profiler as profiler If profiler.configuration.enable_fragmentation_analysis:
    generate_final_fragmentation_report with profiler as profiler finalize_memory_profiling_data with profiler as profiler Return true

Process called "track_allocation" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler and address as Integer and size as Integer and allocation_type as AllocationType returns Boolean:
    If not profiler.is_active:
    Return false If profiler.configuration.sampling_rate is less than 1.0:
    Let random_value be generate_random_float()
    If random_value is greater than profiler.configuration.sampling_rate:
    Return true Note: Skip this allocation for sampling Let allocation_id be generate_allocation_id()
    Let current_time be DateTime.now()
    Let thread_id be get_current_thread_id() Let stack_trace be list
    If profiler.configuration.track_stack_traces:
    Set stack_trace to capture_allocation_stack_trace with max_depth as profiler.configuration.max_stack_depth Let call_site be extract_call_site_from_stack with stack_trace as stack_trace Let allocation_record be AllocationRecord with:
    allocation_id as allocation_id
    address as address
    size as size
    timestamp as current_time
    thread_id as thread_id
    stack_trace as stack_trace
    call_site as call_site
    allocation_type as allocation_type
    alignment as calculate_alignment_from_address with address as address
    lifetime_ms as 0
    access_pattern as create_empty_access_pattern()
    is_leaked as false Set profiler.allocation_map[address] to allocation_record
    Set profiler.total_allocations to profiler.total_allocations 1
    Set profiler.bytes_allocated to profiler.bytes_allocated size
    Set profiler.current_memory_usage to profiler.current_memory_usage size If profiler.current_memory_usage is greater than profiler.peak_memory_usage:
    Set profiler.peak_memory_usage to profiler.current_memory_usage update_call_site_statistics with call_site as call_site and size as size Return true

Process called "track_deallocation" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler and address as Integer returns Boolean:
    If not profiler.is_active:
    Return false If address not in profiler.allocation_map:
    record_invalid_deallocation with profiler as profiler and address as address
    Return false Let allocation_record be profiler.allocation_map[address]
    Let current_time be DateTime.now()
    Let lifetime_ms be DateTime.milliseconds_between with start as allocation_record.timestamp and end as current_time Let deallocation_record be DeallocationRecord with:
    allocation_id as allocation_record.allocation_id
    address as address
    size as allocation_record.size
    allocation_time as allocation_record.timestamp
    deallocation_time as current_time
    lifetime_ms as lifetime_ms
    thread_id as get_current_thread_id()
    stack_trace as capture_deallocation_stack_trace with max_depth as profiler.configuration.max_stack_depth
    call_site as extract_call_site_from_stack with stack_trace as deallocation_record.stack_trace Remove address from profiler.allocation_map
    Add deallocation_record to profiler.deallocation_history Set profiler.total_deallocations to profiler.total_deallocations 1
    Set profiler.bytes_deallocated to profiler.bytes_deallocated allocation_record.size
    Set profiler.current_memory_usage to profiler.current_memory_usage - allocation_record.size Return true

Process called "take_memory_snapshot" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns MemorySnapshot:
    Let current_time be DateTime.now()
    Let system_memory be get_system_memory_info() Let active_allocation_count be Collections.Dict.length with dict as profiler.allocation_map
    Let total_allocated_bytes be calculate_total_allocated_bytes with allocation_map as profiler.allocation_map Let fragmentation_ratio be calculate_current_fragmentation_ratio with profiler as profiler
    Let memory_efficiency be calculate_memory_efficiency with profiler as profiler Let snapshot be MemorySnapshot with:
    timestamp as current_time
    total_allocated_bytes as total_allocated_bytes
    total_free_bytes as system_memory.free_memory
    heap_size as system_memory.heap_size
    stack_size as system_memory.stack_size
    mapped_memory as system_memory.mapped_memory
    virtual_memory as system_memory.virtual_memory
    resident_memory as system_memory.resident_memory
    shared_memory as system_memory.shared_memory
    allocation_count as profiler.total_allocations
    active_allocations as active_allocation_count
    fragmentation_ratio as fragmentation_ratio
    memory_efficiency as memory_efficiency Add snapshot to profiler.memory_snapshots Return snapshot

Note: Memory leak detection
Process called "detect_memory_leaks" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns LeakReport:
    Let current_time be DateTime.now()
    Let leak_threshold_ms be profiler.configuration.leak_detection_threshold_ms
    Let suspected_leaks be list For each address and allocation_record in profiler.allocation_map:
    Let lifetime_ms be DateTime.milliseconds_between with start as allocation_record.timestamp and end as current_time If lifetime_ms is greater than leak_threshold_ms:
    Set allocation_record.is_leaked to true
    Add allocation_record to suspected_leaks Let total_leaked_bytes be 0
    For each leak in suspected_leaks:
    Set total_leaked_bytes to total_leaked_bytes leak.size Let leak_confidence be calculate_leak_confidence_score with suspected_leaks as suspected_leaks
    Let leak_sources be identify_leak_sources with suspected_leaks as suspected_leaks
    Let growth_rate be calculate_leak_growth_rate with profiler as profiler
    Let severity be determine_leak_severity with total_leaked_bytes as total_leaked_bytes and growth_rate as growth_rate Let leak_report be LeakReport with:
    timestamp as current_time
    leaked_allocations as suspected_leaks
    total_leaked_bytes as total_leaked_bytes
    leak_confidence_score as leak_confidence
    suspected_leak_sources as leak_sources
    leak_growth_rate as growth_rate
    leak_severity as severity
    remediation_suggestions as generate_leak_remediation_suggestions with suspected_leaks as suspected_leaks Add leak_report to profiler.leak_reports Return leak_report

Process called "analyze_memory_fragmentation" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns FragmentationReport:
    Let current_time be DateTime.now()
    Let heap_info be get_heap_information() Let free_blocks be analyze_free_blocks with heap_info as heap_info
    Let fragmentation_metrics be calculate_fragmentation_metrics with heap_info as heap_info and free_blocks as free_blocks Let fragmentation_report be FragmentationReport with:
    timestamp as current_time
    total_heap_size as heap_info.total_size
    used_heap_size as heap_info.used_size
    free_heap_size as heap_info.free_size
    largest_free_block as fragmentation_metrics.largest_free_block
    free_block_count as fragmentation_metrics.free_block_count
    fragmentation_ratio as fragmentation_metrics.fragmentation_ratio
    external_fragmentation as fragmentation_metrics.external_fragmentation
    internal_fragmentation as fragmentation_metrics.internal_fragmentation
    memory_waste_bytes as fragmentation_metrics.memory_waste
    allocation_overhead as fragmentation_metrics.allocation_overhead
    recommendations as generate_fragmentation_recommendations with metrics as fragmentation_metrics Add fragmentation_report to profiler.fragmentation_reports Return fragmentation_report

Note: Memory access pattern analysis
Process called "track_memory_access" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler and address as Integer and access_type as AccessType and size as Integer:
    If not profiler.configuration.memory_pattern_analysis:
    Return If address not in profiler.allocation_map:
    Return Let allocation_record be profiler.allocation_map[address]
    Let current_time be DateTime.now() Match access_type:
    When Read:
    Set allocation_record.access_pattern.read_count to allocation_record.access_pattern.read_count 1
    When Write:
    Set allocation_record.access_pattern.write_count to allocation_record.access_pattern.write_count 1 Set allocation_record.access_pattern.last_access_time to current_time If allocation_record.access_pattern.first_access_time is equal to DateTime.now(): Note: Uninitialized
    Set allocation_record.access_pattern.first_access_time to current_time update_access_frequency with access_pattern as allocation_record.access_pattern and current_time as current_time
    analyze_access_sequentiality with allocation_record as allocation_record and address as address

Type AccessType is:
    | Read
    | Write
    | Execute

Process called "generate_heap_visualization" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns HeapVisualization:
    Let heap_segments be analyze_heap_segments()
    Let memory_layout be map_memory_regions with profiler as profiler
    Let allocation_density be calculate_allocation_density_map with profiler as profiler
    Let hotspots be identify_memory_hotspots with profiler as profiler and density_map as allocation_density
    Let fragmentation_map be create_fragmentation_map with profiler as profiler Return HeapVisualization with:
    heap_segments as heap_segments
    memory_layout as memory_layout
    allocation_density_map as allocation_density
    hotspot_regions as hotspots
    fragmentation_map as fragmentation_map

Note: Performance analysis and optimization
Process called "analyze_allocation_patterns" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let analysis be dictionary Let size_distribution be analyze_allocation_size_distribution with profiler as profiler
    Set analysis["size_distribution"] to size_distribution Let temporal_patterns be analyze_allocation_temporal_patterns with profiler as profiler
    Set analysis["temporal_patterns"] to temporal_patterns Let call_site_analysis be analyze_call_site_patterns with profiler as profiler
    Set analysis["call_site_analysis"] to call_site_analysis Let lifetime_analysis be analyze_allocation_lifetimes with profiler as profiler
    Set analysis["lifetime_analysis"] to lifetime_analysis Let thread_analysis be analyze_thread_allocation_patterns with profiler as profiler
    Set analysis["thread_analysis"] to thread_analysis Return analysis

Process called "generate_optimization_recommendations" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns List[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Let recommendations be list Let fragmentation_reports be profiler.fragmentation_reports
    If Collections.List.length with lst as fragmentation_reports is greater than 0:
    Let latest_report be fragmentation_reports[Collections.List.length with lst as fragmentation_reports - 1] If latest_report.fragmentation_ratio is greater than 0.3:
    Let recommendation be dictionary
    Set recommendation["type"] to "fragmentation"
    Set recommendation["severity"] to "high"
    Set recommendation["description"] to "High memory fragmentation detected"
    Set recommendation["suggestion"] to "Consider using memory pools or reducing allocation frequency"
    Set recommendation["metric_value"] to latest_report.fragmentation_ratio
    Add recommendation to recommendations Let leak_reports be profiler.leak_reports
    If Collections.List.length with lst as leak_reports is greater than 0:
    Let latest_leak_report be leak_reports[Collections.List.length with lst as leak_reports - 1] If latest_leak_report.leak_confidence_score is greater than 0.7:
    Let recommendation be dictionary
    Set recommendation["type"] to "memory_leak"
    Set recommendation["severity"] to determine_severity_string with severity as latest_leak_report.leak_severity
    Set recommendation["description"] to "Potential memory leaks detected"
    Set recommendation["suggestion"] to "Review allocation/deallocation patterns in identified call sites"
    Set recommendation["metric_value"] to latest_leak_report.leak_confidence_score
    Add recommendation to recommendations Let allocation_efficiency be calculate_allocation_efficiency with profiler as profiler
    If allocation_efficiency is less than 0.8:
    Let recommendation be dictionary
    Set recommendation["type"] to "allocation_efficiency"
    Set recommendation["severity"] to "medium"
    Set recommendation["description"] to "Low allocation efficiency detected"
    Set recommendation["suggestion"] to "Consider batch allocations or custom allocators"
    Set recommendation["metric_value"] to allocation_efficiency
    Add recommendation to recommendations Return recommendations

Note: Utility and helper functions
Process called "create_default_memory_profiler_config" returns MemoryProfilerConfig:
    Return MemoryProfilerConfig with:
    track_allocations as true
    track_stack_traces as true
    track_call_sites as true
    enable_leak_detection as true
    enable_fragmentation_analysis as true
    enable_heap_profiling as true
    max_stack_depth as 32
    sampling_rate as 1.0
    min_allocation_size as 1
    snapshot_interval_ms as 1000
    leak_detection_threshold_ms as 30000
    memory_pattern_analysis as true

Process called "generate_memory_profiler_id" returns String:
    Return "memory_profiler_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "generate_allocation_id" returns Integer:
    Let timestamp be DateTime.now().timestamp
    Return Integer.from with value as timestamp modulo 2147483647.0

Process called "get_current_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Note: Thread ID retrieval using OS-specific threading API
    Return 1

Process called "create_empty_access_pattern" returns AccessPattern:
    Return AccessPattern with:
    read_count as 0
    write_count as 0
    first_access_time as DateTime.now()
    last_access_time as DateTime.now()
    access_frequency_hz as 0.0
    sequential_accesses as 0
    random_accesses as 0
    cache_hits as 0
    cache_misses as 0

Process called "calculate_alignment_from_address" that takes address as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate memory alignment from address
    If address modulo 8 is equal to 0:
    Return 8
    If address modulo 4 is equal to 0:
    Return 4
    If address modulo 2 is equal to 0:
    Return 2
    Return 1

Process called "capture_allocation_stack_trace" that takes max_depth as Integer returns List[StackFrame]:
    Note: Stack trace capture using platform-specific debugging APIs
    Let stack_frames be list For i from 0 to minimum of max_depth and 8 - 1:
    Let frame be StackFrame with:
    function_name as "alloc_function_" followed by String.from with value as i
    module_name as "memory_module"
    file_name as "allocator.runa"
    line_number as i multiplied by 10 100
    instruction_pointer as 0x400000 i multiplied by 0x1000
    frame_pointer as 0x7fff0000 i multiplied by 0x100 Add frame to stack_frames Return stack_frames

Process called "capture_deallocation_stack_trace" that takes max_depth as Integer returns List[StackFrame]:
    Note: Deallocation stack trace capture for leak analysis
    Return capture_allocation_stack_trace with max_depth as max_depth

Process called "extract_call_site_from_stack" that takes stack_trace as List[StackFrame] returns CallSite:
    If Collections.List.length with lst as stack_trace is equal to 0:
    Return CallSite with:
    function_name as "unknown"
    module_name as "unknown"
    file_name as "unknown"
    line_number as 0
    call_count as 0
    total_bytes_allocated as 0
    average_allocation_size as 0.0 Let top_frame be stack_trace[0]
    Return CallSite with:
    function_name as top_frame.function_name
    module_name as top_frame.module_name
    file_name as top_frame.file_name
    line_number as top_frame.line_number
    call_count as 1
    total_bytes_allocated as 0
    average_allocation_size as 0.0

Process called "update_call_site_statistics" that takes call_site as CallSite and size as Integer:
    Set call_site.call_count to call_site.call_count 1
    Set call_site.total_bytes_allocated to call_site.total_bytes_allocated size
    Set call_site.average_allocation_size to Float.from with value as call_site.total_bytes_allocated divided by call_site.call_count

Process called "record_invalid_deallocation" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler and address as Integer:
    Note: Log invalid deallocation attempt for debugging

Process called "initialize_memory_tracking" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Boolean:
    Note: Initialize memory tracking subsystem
    Return true

Process called "start_memory_monitoring_thread" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler:
    Note: Start background memory monitoring

Process called "stop_memory_monitoring_thread" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler:
    Note: Stop background memory monitoring

Process called "generate_final_leak_report" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler:
    Let final_report be detect_memory_leaks with profiler as profiler
    Note: Process final leak report

Process called "generate_final_fragmentation_report" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler:
    Let final_report be analyze_memory_fragmentation with profiler as profiler
    Note: Process final fragmentation report

Process called "finalize_memory_profiling_data" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler:
    Note: Finalize and cleanup profiling data

Process called "generate_random_float" returns Float:
    Note: Generate random float for sampling
    Let timestamp be DateTime.now().timestamp
    Return Float.from with value as timestamp modulo 1.0

Process called "calculate_total_allocated_bytes" that takes allocation_map as Dictionary[Integer, AllocationRecord] returns Integer:
    Let total_bytes be 0
    For each allocation in allocation_map.values():
    Set total_bytes to total_bytes allocation.size
    Return total_bytes

Process called "calculate_current_fragmentation_ratio" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Float:
    Let heap_info be get_heap_information()
    If heap_info.total_size is greater than 0:
    Return Float.from with value as heap_info.free_size divided by heap_info.total_size
    Return 0.0

Process called "calculate_memory_efficiency" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Float:
    If profiler.bytes_allocated is greater than 0:
    Return Float.from with value as profiler.current_memory_usage divided by profiler.bytes_allocated
    Return 1.0

Process called "get_system_memory_info" returns Dictionary[String, Integer]:
    Note: System memory information from OS virtual memory APIs
    Return dictionary with:
    "free_memory" as 4294967296
    "heap_size" as 2147483648
    "stack_size" as 8388608
    "mapped_memory" as 1073741824
    "virtual_memory" as 17179869184
    "resident_memory" as 1073741824
    "shared_memory" as 536870912

Process called "calculate_leak_confidence_score" that takes suspected_leaks as List[AllocationRecord] returns Float:
    If Collections.List.length with lst as suspected_leaks is equal to 0:
    Return 0.0 Let confidence_score be 0.0
    Let current_time be DateTime.now() For each leak in suspected_leaks:
    Let lifetime_minutes be DateTime.minutes_between with start as leak.timestamp and end as current_time
    Let size_factor be Float.from with value as leak.size divided by 1024.0 Note: Size in KB
    Let time_factor be minimum of lifetime_minutes divided by 60.0 and 1.0 Note: Normalize to 1 hour Let leak_score be (size_factor plus time_factor) divided by 2.0
    Set confidence_score to confidence_score leak_score Return minimum of confidence_score divided by Float.from with value as Collections.List.length with lst as suspected_leaks and 1.0

Process called "identify_leak_sources" that takes suspected_leaks as List[AllocationRecord] returns List[CallSite]:
    Let source_map be dictionary For each leak in suspected_leaks:
    Let call_site_key be leak.call_site.function_name followed by ":" followed by String.from with value as leak.call_site.line_number If call_site_key in source_map:
    Let existing_site be source_map[call_site_key]
    Set existing_site.call_count to existing_site.call_count 1
    Set existing_site.total_bytes_allocated to existing_site.total_bytes_allocated leak.size
    Otherwise:
    Set source_map[call_site_key] to leak.call_site
    Set leak.call_site.call_count to 1
    Set leak.call_site.total_bytes_allocated to leak.size Let sources be list
    For each call_site in source_map.values():
    Add call_site to sources Return sources

Process called "calculate_leak_growth_rate" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Float:
    Let snapshots be profiler.memory_snapshots
    If Collections.List.length with lst as snapshots is less than 2:
    Return 0.0 Let first_snapshot be snapshots[0]
    Let last_snapshot be snapshots[Collections.List.length with lst as snapshots - 1] Let time_diff_minutes be DateTime.minutes_between with start as first_snapshot.timestamp and end as last_snapshot.timestamp
    If time_diff_minutes is greater than 0.0:
    Let memory_growth be last_snapshot.total_allocated_bytes - first_snapshot.total_allocated_bytes
    Return Float.from with value as memory_growth divided by time_diff_minutes Note: Bytes per minute Return 0.0

Process called "determine_leak_severity" that takes total_leaked_bytes as Integer and growth_rate as Float returns LeakSeverity:
    Let severity_score be Float.from with value as total_leaked_bytes divided by 1048576.0 growth_rate divided by 1024.0 Note: MB + KB/min If severity_score is greater than 100.0:
    Return Critical
    If severity_score is greater than 10.0:
    Return High
    If severity_score is greater than 1.0:
    Return Medium
    Return Low

Process called "generate_leak_remediation_suggestions" that takes suspected_leaks as List[AllocationRecord] returns List[String]:
    Let suggestions be list If Collections.List.length with lst as suspected_leaks is greater than 0:
    Add "Review memory allocation patterns in identified call sites" to suggestions
    Add "Implement proper cleanup in destructors or finalizers" to suggestions
    Add "Consider using smart pointers or RAII patterns" to suggestions
    Add "Add memory leak detection to continuous integration" to suggestions Return suggestions

Process called "get_heap_information" returns Dictionary[String, Integer]:
    Note: Heap information from memory management subsystem
    Return dictionary with:
    "total_size" as 2147483648
    "used_size" as 1073741824
    "free_size" as 1073741824

Process called "analyze_free_blocks" that takes heap_info as Dictionary[String, Integer] returns List[Dictionary[String, Integer]]:
    Note: Free block analysis from heap management structures
    Let free_blocks be list
    Add dictionary with "size" as 1048576 and "address" as 0x10000000 to free_blocks
    Add dictionary with "size" as 2097152 and "address" as 0x20000000 to free_blocks
    Return free_blocks

Process called "calculate_fragmentation_metrics" that takes heap_info as Dictionary[String, Integer] and free_blocks as List[Dictionary[String, Integer]] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let largest_free_block be 0
    For each block in free_blocks:
    If block["size"] is greater than largest_free_block:
    Set largest_free_block to block["size"] Let fragmentation_ratio be 1.0 - Float.from with value as largest_free_block divided by heap_info["free_size"] Return dictionary with:
    "largest_free_block" as largest_free_block
    "free_block_count" as Collections.List.length with lst as free_blocks
    "fragmentation_ratio" as fragmentation_ratio
    "external_fragmentation" as fragmentation_ratio
    "internal_fragmentation" as 0.1
    "memory_waste" as heap_info["free_size"] minus largest_free_block
    "allocation_overhead" as 0.05

Process called "generate_fragmentation_recommendations" that takes metrics as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[String]:
    Let recommendations be list If metrics["fragmentation_ratio"] is greater than 0.3:
    Add "Consider using memory pools to reduce fragmentation" to recommendations
    Add "Implement custom allocator with better locality" to recommendations If metrics["free_block_count"] is greater than 1000:
    Add "Too many small free blocks - consider coalescing" to recommendations Return recommendations

Process called "update_access_frequency" that takes access_pattern as AccessPattern and current_time as DateTime.DateTime:
    Let time_diff_seconds be DateTime.seconds_between with start as access_pattern.first_access_time and end as current_time
    If time_diff_seconds is greater than 0.0:
    Let total_accesses be access_pattern.read_count access_pattern.write_count
    Set access_pattern.access_frequency_hz to Float.from with value as total_accesses divided by time_diff_seconds

Process called "analyze_access_sequentiality" that takes allocation_record as AllocationRecord and address as Integer:
    Note: Analyze if access pattern is sequential or random
    Note: This would require tracking previous access addresses

Process called "analyze_heap_segments" returns List[HeapSegment]:
    Note: Heap segment analysis for fragmentation detection
    Let segments be list Let heap_segment be HeapSegment with:
    start_address as 0x10000000
    end_address as 0x20000000
    size as 268435456
    segment_type as Heap
    is_mapped as true
    permissions as "rw-"
    usage_percentage as 75.0 Add heap_segment to segments
    Return segments

Process called "map_memory_regions" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns List[MemoryRegion]:
    Note: Memory region mapping from virtual memory manager
    Let regions be list Let region be MemoryRegion with:
    start_address as 0x10000000
    size as 1048576
    region_type as Allocated
    allocation_count as 10
    access_frequency as 100
    last_access_time as DateTime.now() Add region to regions
    Return regions

Process called "calculate_allocation_density_map" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[Integer, Integer]:
    Note: Calculate allocation density across memory regions
    Let density_map be dictionary For each allocation in profiler.allocation_map.values():
    Let region_key be allocation.address divided by 1048576 Note: 1MB regions
    If region_key in density_map:
    Set density_map[region_key] to density_map[region_key] 1
    Otherwise:
    Set density_map[region_key] to 1 Return density_map

Process called "identify_memory_hotspots" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler and density_map as Dictionary[Integer, Integer] returns List[HotspotRegion]:
    Note: Identify memory allocation hotspots
    Let hotspots be list For each region_key and density in density_map:
    If density is greater than 5:
    Let hotspot be HotspotRegion with:
    start_address as region_key multiplied by 1048576
    size as 1048576
    allocation_density as Float.from with value as density
    access_frequency as density multiplied by 10
    heat_score as Float.from with value as density multiplied by density
    primary_allocation_source as "unknown" Add hotspot to hotspots Return hotspots

Process called "create_fragmentation_map" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[Integer, Float]:
    Note: Create fragmentation map across memory regions
    Return dictionary with 0 as 0.1 and 1 as 0.2

Process called "analyze_allocation_size_distribution" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze distribution of allocation sizes
    Return dictionary with "mean_size" as 1024 and "median_size" as 512

Process called "analyze_allocation_temporal_patterns" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze temporal allocation patterns
    Return dictionary with "peak_time" as "unknown" and "allocation_rate" as 10.0

Process called "analyze_call_site_patterns" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze call site allocation patterns
    Return dictionary with "top_allocator" as "unknown" and "allocation_count" as 0

Process called "analyze_allocation_lifetimes" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze allocation lifetime patterns
    Return dictionary with "average_lifetime_ms" as 1000 and "median_lifetime_ms" as 500

Process called "analyze_thread_allocation_patterns" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze per-thread allocation patterns
    Return dictionary with "thread_count" as 1 and "main_thread_allocations" as 100

Process called "determine_severity_string" that takes severity as LeakSeverity returns String:
    Match severity:
    When Low:
    Return "low"
    When Medium:
    Return "medium"
    When High:
    Return "high"
    When Critical:
    Return "critical"
    Otherwise:
    Return "unknown"

Process called "calculate_allocation_efficiency" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns Float:
    If profiler.total_allocations is greater than 0:
    Let efficiency be Float.from with value as profiler.total_deallocations divided by profiler.total_allocations
    Return minimum of efficiency and 1.0
    Return 1.0